In these and many similar texts, e.g., 2 Thess.
ii, 13, it is difficult to decide whether the saint spoken
of is the Holy Ghost or the sanctified spirit of man.
However, the spirit of man is sanctified only by the
action, and even indwelling, of the; Holy Ghost.

